{
  "stem": "3022.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "One day on my on my work detail, the Polish-- the man who manned the machine, the Polish worker, the civilian worker who used to come and didn't show up.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "So I had to do his shift and then do my shift again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "So I was on my shift for 36 hours.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Towards the end of my, my 36-- the shift, I got very sleepy, very tired, couldn't keep my eyes up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And I was afraid I was going to ruin the work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And if I ruin work, you know, I was a dead man.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went, and I laid down to sleep.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found the place between the black-out curtains, because the lights was always blacked out by, by, by long black curtains in the window.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one of the guards, or the [NON-ENGLISH] that, that patrolled the premises, happened to have been one of the meanest guard.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His name was Podolnyi, saw my silhouette between the curtains and the window.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he came into the shop, and pulled me out, and administered a severe beating, to the point that he broke the, the woodstock on his, you know, on his gun, on his carbine.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Finally, somebody went and ran to the German supervisor, who rescued me, pulled me out, because I was a valuable, you know, defense worker.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was only two people who knew to operate the machine, and he pulled me out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I felt that I had to get out from this particular detail, because we had a very, very-- on the day shift where I worked.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Actually, on the night shift that I worked, because this happened, you know, at night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The day shift was manned by the Polish worker.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
